  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Junior Investment Analyst Specialist",
  "description": "<p>We are partnering with an Asset Management whom are seeking a <strong>Junior Alternative Investments Specialist</strong> to support the evaluation, execution, and ongoing monitoring of alternative investment opportunities. This role is ideal for candidates at an early stage of their career who are eager to gain hands-on exposure across private markets, including fund and investment lifecycle activities.</p><p>The successful candidate will work closely with senior investment professionals and management, supporting analysis, documentation, and coordination with both internal teams and external service providers.<br /></p><p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Work closely with senior investment professionals on ad hoc projects and new initiatives</li><li>Perform cash flow modelling, IRR calculations, and financial modelling</li><li>Assist with the preparation of investment summaries, internal notes and presentation materials </li><li>Coordinate with external service providers such as fund administrators, custodians and auditors </li><li>Involve in the full fund cycle such as setting up, monitoring and closing of fund</li><li>Assist with preparation of regulatory documentation and compliance checks </li><li>Support documentation and follow up </li><li>Track follow-ups, scheduling meetings with investors </li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Bachelor's degree in Finance or Economics is preferred </li><li>Strong interest in alternative investment space such as Private Equity, Private Credit or Real Estate</li><li>Open to Fresh Grad with internship experience within the private alternative space </li><li>Prior exposure to financial modelling in a professional or internship setting is required</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Simply click the 'Apply now\" button to get started.</strong></p><p><strong>EA License No.</strong> 23S2077</p><p><strong>EA Reg No.</strong>: R22104987</p>",
